Did he just touch that thing?"
[ Rolling Guide ]
As far as I know, both Avrae and Sidekick do not mimic the bonus and penalty dice mechanic of Call of Cthulhu. They will simply roll two instances of a d100. When you are told to make the roll with bonus/penalty dice, use the command rolling for 2 or more d10 dice, based on the amount of the bonus/penalty dice, and keep the lowest (for bonus die)/the highest (for penalty die), and another d10, ignoring the addition result. For example, a roll with 1 bonus die is rolled with the command !roll 2d10kl1+1d10: the second die is "unit" die, and the ones on front are "tens" dice. A 10 on a die is a 0; unless if both is a 10, which is then read as 100. For normal roll, just use the command for a d100 instead.
 (edited)

The building before you stands with ferocity. Its black, sleek body scrapes the sky above, like a dark claw of a predator. Layers and layers of floors, stacked atop one another, like a feast to a hungry beast. The giant names itself as Hotel Virgato, possibly a made-up name, a name to boost its shallow pride.
You will face it, enter through its vine, and meet its heart: someone that you know well, your goal of today, the reason why you are here. Arthur Pendleton. Oh, his name. You know him, varyingly. He can be said as a pillar of your life. Without him, maybe you can crumble apart. Yet, without confronting him, a hole in your chest is going to gape further.
With a letter sealed in deep blue wax, you go forward.
"As you are, I was, As I am, so you shall also be."
You are you, each of your own person, having different lives, but are utterly useless in the grand scheme of all. But you believe you have a purpose, so let us pretend it to be so and come at me. The red thread of fate has been spun.   Either you are a police detective that attempts to arrest me for the crimes that yes I did and still do, with your assortments of weaponry and your love for rock; either you are a prostitute that attempts to behead me with your charm due to my insincere promises and your unsatisfied lust, a cold iron collar on your gentle hands; either you are calling yourself as my daughter, a self-proclaimed occultist, who wish to be with me despite your hideous figure, who is blessed by luck, and either my adversary or my ally; either you are my best friend and almost a father figure, a bartender that mixes drinks and changes lives, except those are not mine, but still wishing for it to be so;   come to me, in my room, Hotel Virgato, Room 1302.   Let us have a game.  
Yours Truly [ Arthur Pendleton ]
